T1  - A New Look at Stigmatization in and of Organizations
AU  - Paetzold, Ramona L.
AU  - Dipboye, Robert L.
AU  - Elsbach, Kimberly D.
Y1  - 2008/01/01
PY  - 2008
DA  - 2008/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2008.27752576
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2008.27752576
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 186
EP  - 193
VL  - 33
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Although stigma has been studied extensively in psychology and sociology, there has been little research on stigmatization in organizational settings. This special topic forum, which includes four articles, builds on previous social science research and expands its coverage both to individuals within organizations and to organizations themselves. As we note here, these four articles provide an opportunity to examine not only the harm caused by stigma but its potential benefits as well.
AB  - Although stigma has been studied extensively in psychology and sociology, there has been little research on stigmatization in organizational settings. This special topic forum, which includes four articles, builds on previous social science research and expands its coverage both to individuals within organizations and to organizations themselves. As we note here, these four articles provide an opportunity to examine not only the harm caused by stigma but its potential benefits as well.
SN  - 0363-7425
